item.title: Favorite non-Auxy tracks of 2017
item.dc:creator: DontPartyWithGuns
item.description:
Here goes…

I have so many songs that I’ve listened to and liked so Im gonna be different and list My Top 3 EPs/LPs/Albums That I Found This Year That I Recommend You Check Out In No Particular Order.

  1. Endless Fantasy by Anamanaguchi (2013)
    https://youtu.be/euTyRhnqFtA?list=PLkQKpzRGtPP9uzgsEOekO6LCjRJqHyDyw
    I cannot explain how much this LP means to me. It has introduced me to Anamanaguchi which is one of my favorite bands and really changed the way I view music production. Basically, if you like chiptune or indie rock (or both) then this LP will make you crazy with happiness. The Endless Fantasy LP combines old video game synth sounds with modern guitars and drums and effects.
    ~
    Two songs I recommend from it are Snow Angels (the melody in this is way too catchy), Endless Fantasy (even more catchy), and Planet (omg planet abkehfbbljgavlbia).

[ Also quick fun fact; for the music video of Endless Fantasy, the members of Anamanaguchi superglued a piece of pizza to a weather balloon and sent it of to space (while recording it with a strapped on camera of course). They also got fined for it because its illegal to send balloons that size into space in New York without a permit or smthn idk. It also landed in someone’s yard in New Jersey and they thought it was a bomb cause it fell with such impact. ]

  1. Alive In Screen by nelward (2017)
    https://youtu.be/Ib9JIRu_WKU?list=PLeiwnwcPb0cQGGO5oPLS6HF-p1MWiF14m
    Nelward is one of those artists that make you wonder what you’re doing with your life. Alive In Screen showcases his abilities in making very creative music. Also it has funky lyrics like “ooh! u blew ur load before u even began, ur better off jumping out of a van, and tryna land on a tight rope” from ‘the minus world’ (i kid you not those are the actual lyrics lmao). So, if you ever get tired of listening to music with similar patterns and synths or whatnot, listen to this, you’ll question everything you’ve ever done with your life.
    ~
    Three songs I recommend from Alive In Screen are seafoam breeze (which has more of nelward’s chill side which is nice), the minus world (idek how to explain this one, just take a listen for yourself), and apple shampoo (if nelward could be a popstar, then this would be his most popular song. its funky has catchy lyrics, and is overall fun.)

  2. A Moment In Time EP by Droeloe (2017)
    https://youtu.be/p7pkk3rnRDk?list=PL78C9nyy_1bvLYwdPk4dKU5ELEAxRg8ZC
    Droeloe has always been one of my favorite artists and this EP proved even more how talented they are. They always use a specific set of synths at least once in their songs. These sounds range from a music box to a special pluck noise they’ve made and they all make their songs seem childish in a way. It makes it seem like their songs are coming from the heart and are snapshots of the past. That especially helps for this EP because its about how they started at humble pasts and how they’re going home and reliving old memories.
    ~
    The three tracks from this EP that I recommend are Sunburn (which is about the rollercoaster between the ups and downs of love), Lilypads (which is about a smell or a place that brings back an old memory, and is my personal favorite from the EP), and Homebound (I cant really summarize the meaning of this one so here is their official explanation (c+p from description on soundcloud); ‘Living your life while running away from yourself can feel like an endless journey, getting closer to accepting who you are sometimes even more so. but the latter can improve your empowering sense of destination and ambition along the way. it’s ok to feel sad, lonely or angry, as long as you realise it’s timely too. this is the feeling we tried to convey with “Homebound”’).

item.title: Favorite non-Auxy tracks of 2017
item.dc:creator: iammane
item.description:
Gonna date myself here, don’t care. In no particular order:

Aphex Twin - Windowlicker (such a classic, classic track, awesome video. Kids please don’t watch and if you do, you didn’t hear this from me)
Squarepusher - My Red Hot Car (another totally awesome one from before the millenium, or thereabouts)
BT - 1.618 (a bit long, but daaaamn once it takes off it’s pretty incredible).

If I was supposed to pick stuff from 2017 sorry, I failed. These songs are all like 10+, almost 20 years old (for Aphex and Squarepusher). Sorry.
